{
  "texts": [
    "AI can augment worker creativity by freeing the worker from codifiable and repetitive tasks (Tsang and Almirall 2021), allowing the worker to attend to more complex problem solving, as in the case of telemarketers (Jia et al. 2023).",
    "Digitalization makes in silico experimentation or simulation easier and cheaper.",
    "Social IntelligenceAlso called \"noncognitive skills\" (Kautz et al.",
    "2014; Sánchez-Puerta et al. 2016), social intelligence refers to character traits key to management, such as leadership, persuasion, negotiation or bargaining, collaboration, empathy, and care.",
    "As AI does more \"thinking\" (\"calculating\" would be more precise), humans can focus on feeling, empathy, and emotions, the lubricants for interpersonal relationships (Rust and Huang 2021)."
  ]
}